PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:164:To make testing easier, the server should expose both a unified route and strict test aliases.
PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:168:| `/mcp` | Accepts None, Basic, or OAuth. Auth method is inferred from request headers. |
PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:169:| `/mcp/none` | Requires no auth. Useful for explicit no-auth tests. |
PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:170:| `/mcp/basic` | Requires valid Basic Auth. Missing/invalid Basic Auth returns `401`. |
PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:171:| `/mcp/oauth` | Requires valid Bearer token. Missing/invalid token returns `401`; insufficient endpoint permission returns `403`. |
PRD/mcp_mock_server_prd.md:173:This avoids ambiguity during tests. For example, an MCP client that claims to be testing OAuth can be pointed to `/mcp/oauth`, while a client testing no-auth can be pointed to `/mcp/none`.
